&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ESSEX PARTNERSHIP UNIVERSITY NHS TRUST&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SPECIALIST PSYCHOSIS TEAM - NORTH EAST ESSEX&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;COMMUNITY MENTAL HEALTH NURSE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AFC BAND 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HOURS : 37.5 per week &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a vacancies in our Specialist Psychosis Team. However, please note that North Essex community mental health services are in the midst of an exciting transformation project and our services will in the near future will be remodelled into a Colchester treatment team and Tendring treatment team. Successful applicants will have the opportunity to offer a preference in which location they would like to practice. You will be working&lt;span&gt; with service users with complex and enduring needs offering specialist interventions for the treatment of serious mental illness, personality disorder, and common mental health conditions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced, dynamic and enthusiastic Mental Health Nurse with excellent communication and organisational skills, experience in carrying out comprehensive assessments of patients’ needs, and who is fully committed to working in a multi disciplinary team setting. You must have an awareness of current health and social care issues that affect community care and people with significant mental health needs. You must be committed to working in partnership with clients/carers and a range of other care staff and agencies to provide truly person centred services.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In return you will benefit from excellent clinical supervision and working within a diverse multi-professional team. This post also offers the opportunity to work in conjunction with our newly developing Primary Care Networks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Trust is an Equal Opportunities Employer. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We particularly welcome applications from people with experience of using mental health services.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EPUT are looking for motivated staff who share our Trust values; Open, Compassionate and Empowering. In return, EPUT can offer you a range of benefits and development including;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Season Ticket Loans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts for staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent Training facilities and opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Buying and Selling annual leave scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to work bank shifts and expand knowledge and experience in other areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary Sacrifice schemes including lease cars and Cycle to Work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameBen GentlemanJob titleClinical ManagerEmail addressbenjamin.gentleman1@nhs.netTelephone number07583126188&lt;/p&gt;
